         <abstract><p>This is the general
            record for the Gadl of St Libānos (Maṭāʿ), to be used in cases where the recension
            cannot be identified. The Gadl exists in three different recensions: the first recension
            (<ref type="work" corresp="LIT7615GadLib1"/>); the second recension, which is the most frequent one
            (<ref type="work" corresp="LIT7616GadLib2"/>); the third recension (<ref type="work" corresp="LIT7617GadLib3"/>).
            The text is attributed to ʾElyās, the Bishop of Aksum (cp. <ref type="mss" corresp="ESmgm012"></ref>, 
            <locus target="#17ra">17ra</locus>).</p></abstract>
